In celebration of the 20th anniversary of Non Phixion’s seminal LP, The Future Is Now, Uncle Howie Records is pleased to announce the release of 3 special anniversary edition pressings.

The vocal album boasts a never before revealed, updated version
of the album cover designed by revered illustrator, Mear One.  The 2XLP is pressed on orchid colored discs and are contained within full color sleeves abound with liner notes.

The instrumental LP jacket features an overhauled version of the left half of the never before seen ‘final’ mural illustrated by Mear One.  This release marks the first time the instrumentals have been made available on vinyl in nearly 20 years!

The acappella version of the album features the right half of the 'final' mural, which when put side by side with the instrumental vinyl gives you the full 'final' mural, making this a true collector’s edition to reel in the milestone!  This is also the first time ever that the acappellas have been made available.

This will be the only time these versions will be available with these covers.

Available for pre-order now at www.fatbeats.com and www.hhv.de

The 20th anniversary editions of The Future Is Now are set for release on March 24th via Uncle Howie Records in partnership with Fat Beats Distribution.

@illb1ll @johnsabacredfuentes @thelordgore @djeclipsersc @unclehowie @fatbeats @hhvrecords

The only way to get through this is to remember the good times.

My condolences to the Jolicoeur family @wearedelasoul @plugwondelasoul @inmaseowetrust and the whole Native Tongues crew.  We love ya’ll.

💔🙏🏼🕊️

Another great one has left us.  R.I.P. to Double J of the Flavor Unit (seen here all the way to the left). Had the honor of meeting him just a few months ago at The 45 King’s birthday party.

This whole crew isn’t mentioned nearly enough when talking about all-time great crews.  Their output with The 45 King at the helm took them from the 80s and into the 90s delivering classics from Wild Pitch, Tuff City and Tommy Boy (amongst other labels). You couldn’t listen to a Red Alert show during this era without hearing something from one of them. 

J was incredibly dope (press play) as was all of them.  My condolences to his family, the whole Flavor Unit (peace Lak & Rob) and especially to The 45 King. 💔🙏🏼

#RIPDoubleJ #RIPApache #RIPMarkeyFresh

"Strange Universe was birthed amongst numerous blunted, Colt 45 malt liquor-fueled sessions Non Phixion had with MF DOOM at their
"Area 51" studio in Canarsie, Brooklyn in 1998. Necro provided the beat, which everyone agreed sounded like something DOOM might have made. It was one of the first songs recorded for
